<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Floating replaced elements with auto left and right</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="HTMLonly" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify that if margin left or right are computed as auto their used value is 0." />
        <style type="text/css">
            textarea
            {
                float: left;
                width: 96px;
                height: 96px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                background-color: blue;
                border: solid 1px blue;
                overflow: hidden;
            }
            .c1
            {
                float: left;
                background: green;
                width: 96px;
                height: 96px;
            }
            p
            {
                clear: left;
            }
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div>
            <div class="c1"></div>
            <textarea cols="1" rows="1"></textarea>
            <div class="c1"></div>
        </div>
        <p>Test passes if no white space exists between the green boxes and the blue box.</p>
    </body>
</html>